<h2>Font family</h2>

<p>Both main <code>font-family</code>'s are defined as <a href="{{ '/tokens' | url }}">design tokens</a> keys and provided as CSS custom properties. Those in return are available as utility classes:
<ul>
  <li><code>.text-heading</code> (inherits <code>--font-family-heading</code>)</li>
  <li><code>.text-base</code> (inherits <code>--font-family-base</code>)</li>
</ul>

<p>By default, <code>--font-family-heading</code> is applied to all headline elements (<code>h1</code> – <code>h6</code>). All other elements default to <code>--font-family-base</code>, which is applied to the document element.</p>

{% snippet %}
<p class="text-heading text-l">Heading</p>
<p class="text-base">Text-level</p>
{% endsnippet %}

<h2>Font sizes</h2>

<p>To customize the <code>font-size</code> on an element level, eight utilities classes are on hand for you to use. For all of them, responsive classes are available that use the same viewport width breakpoints as the grid system.</p>

{% snippet %}
<p class="text-xs">XSmall text</p>
<p class="text-s">Small text</p>
<p class="text-m">Medium text (default)</p>
<p class="text-l">Large text</p>
<p class="text-xl">XLarge text</p>
<p class="text-xxl">XXLarge text</p>
<p class="text-xxxl">XXXLarge text</p>
<p class="text-hero">Hero-sized text</p>

<p class="text-m text-xl@sm">XLarge text on small viewports or wider</p>
<p class="text-m text-xl@md">XLarge text on medium viewports or wider</p>
<p class="text-m text-xl@lg">XLarge text on large viewports or wider</p>
{% endsnippet %}

